reviewText: Nice to buy good and cheap movies.
Just a replacement for a VHS.
Invisible Mom. The DVD arrived on Time. I Liked the Movie. I Highly Recommend it. Thanks.
I love the movie. very funny, great movie for the whole family. would recommend to anyone with children. they would love it.
As with all movies of this type, it is the unbelievable, impossible happenings put in an order that entertains..The plot is thin.
This was a great video to watch with my children. It got them interested in science and we enjoyed family time together.

This movie was pretty good, kinda childish at times, but what do you expect?  Trenton Knight was enjoyable as the young son, Josh. But Invisible Mom #2 was an absolute bomb; it was about as entertaining as watching paint dry.  Even tho I'm a fan of Justin Berfield, even he couldn't save it from mediocrity.

Only the laughs are invisible in this tedious, unfunny comedy. Director Fred OlenRay sets a new low, and for the director of "Bad Girls from Mars," that's saying something! It's very sad to see Dee Wallace  Stone, best known from "E.T.," reduced to a film of such  nonexistent ambitions.
